The paper deals with communication algorithms in a network with limited communication capabilities, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of beeps and silence for communication suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The algorithms presented involve graph traversal and message dissemination, which are common topics in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimality of the algorithms, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper emphasizes the practicality and efficiency of the algorithms, which aligns with the focus of social and information networks (cs.SI).
